        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 13 at 2:09PM CDT by NWS Memphis TN</headline>
        <description>At 208 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Crawfordsville, or near Marion, moving east at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
West Memphis, Marion, Earle, Meeman Shelby Forest State Park,
Memphis, Crawfordsville, Sunset, Jericho, Jennette, Downtown Memphis,
Turrell, Clarkedale, Mound City, Booker, Gammon, Cunningham Corner,
St Clair, Harvard, Briark, and Locke.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
